Frontend conventions:
- Nuxt 3 provides auto imports, so theres no need to manually import things like 'ref', 'useState', or 'useRouter'.
- Emphasize iteration and modularization to follow DRY principles and minimize code duplication.
- Use the Composition API when writing Vue components with: <script setup lang="ts">
- Use Composables to encapsulate and share reusable client-side logic or state across multiple components in your Nuxt application.
- Use Nuxt UI, daisyUI and Tailwind CSS for components and styling.
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS; use a mobile-first approach.
- Use @main.css for app theme configuration.
- For images use the <NuxtImage> or <NuxtPicture> components.
- For icons use <Icon> components from the Nuxt Icons module.

Fetching Data:
- Use useFetch for standard data fetching in components. 

- Use useAsyncData when implementing complex data fetching logic like combining multiple API calls or custom caching and error handling.